<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,255,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
<bibRef pageId="3" pageNumber="200" type="book">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1423616961" collectorName="Interestingly, A. &amp; de Juin" country="Greece" location="Greece" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" specimenCount="1">
<author box="[151,325,325,348]" fns="I" npo="LF" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
<collectorName box="[151,325,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Interestingly, A.</collectorName>
</author>
<title box="[333,1157,325,348]" jopScore="0.11591255" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Brullé in his book even gave some ecological indications about this species</title>
“ 
<journalOrPublisher jopScore="0.33589542" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
Au mois 
<collectorName box="[1278,1356,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">de Juin</collectorName>
sur les arbres…” (
<bibRefCitation author="Brulle" box="[268,404,360,383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Brulle, G. A. (1833) I. re Partie. Zoologie. Deuxieme Section. Des animaux articules. In: Bory de Saint-Vincent J. B. G. M. 1832 - 1836 - Expedition scientifique de Moree. Section des sciences physiques, III. Levrault F. L., Paris, Strasbourg (France), 400 pp + pl. i - lxxxiii." type="book chapter" year="1833">Brullé, 1833</bibRefCitation>
) and actually the members of the genus 
<emphasis box="[832,952,359,383]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Zopherisca</emphasis>
Emeljanov do occur on 
<emphasis box="[1212,1407,359,383]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Quercus coccifera</emphasis>
L. in 
<collectingCountry box="[178,253,394,417]" name="Greece" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Greece</collectingCountry>
as it was observed for 
<emphasis box="[499,636,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Z. penelopae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola" box="[651,805,394,417]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Dlabola J. (1974) Zur Taxonomie und Chorologie einiger mediterraner Zikaden. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientarum Hungaricae, 20 (3 - 4), 289 - 308." type="journal article" year="1974">Dlabola, 1974</bibRefCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Gnezdilov" box="[826,1009,394,417]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Gnezdilov V. M. (2015) Notes on Mycterodus drosopoulosi Dlabola, 1982 (Hemiptera, Fulgoroidea, Issidae). Eurasian Entomological Journal, 14 (3), 293 - 295." type="journal article" year="2015">Gnezdilov, 2015</bibRefCitation>
)
</journalOrPublisher>
.
</materialsCitation>
</bibRef>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="200" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,255,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
The whole work of &quot;Expédition scientifique de Morée&quot; started to appear in 1832 and was finished in 1836. In his catalogue 
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf" box="[264,482,464,487]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1958) Fulgoroidea. Issidae. General catalogue of the Homoptera. Fasc. 4. Pt. 15. Baltimore: Waverly Press., 561 pp." type="book" year="1958">Z.P. Metcalf (1958)</bibRefCitation>
kept the first year 1832. However, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Sherborn" box="[1038,1380,464,487]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Sherborn, C. D. &amp; Woodward, B. B. (1901) Dates of publication of the zoological and botanical portions of some French voyages. Part II. Annales &amp; Magasin of Natural History, 8 (7), 333 - 336." type="journal article" year="1901">Sherborn &amp; Woodward (1901)</bibRefCitation>
, text description and plate figure were published separately. Text description of 
<taxonomicName box="[943,1068,497,521]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Issus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[943,1068,497,521]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Issus analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is on page 107 and 108, which are part of livraison 14. According to these authors livraisons 1–16 of text were out by 
<date box="[1067,1180,533,556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="1833-06">June 1833</date>
, and only doubtfully in 
<date box="[151,305,568,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="1832-10">October 1832</date>
. Plate XXXI was published later, in 1834. Accordingly, date of description of the species should be therefore changed to 1833.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,255,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1423616959" country="Croatia" county="Southern Bulgaria" location="Southeastern Greece" municipality="Northwestern Greece" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Peloponnesus">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Emeljanov, 2001" authorityName="Emeljanov" authorityYear="2001" box="[316,623,636,660]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Zopherisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[316,436,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Zopherisca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Emeljanov" box="[443,623,637,660]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Emeljanov A. F. (2001) Fixation of the type species for the genus Latilica Emeljanov, 1971, with description of a new genus of issids (Homoptera, Cicadina: Issidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 9 (1), 99 - 100." type="journal article" year="2001">Emeljanov, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[637,714,637,660]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Issidae</taxonomicName>
) is endemic to Balkan Peninsula (
<bibRefCitation author="Gnezdilov" box="[1078,1431,637,660]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Gnezdilov, V. M. &amp; Drosopoulos, S. (2006) A new species and a new subspecies of the planthopper family Issidae (Hemiptera, Fulgoroidea) from Greece. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 85 (4), 774 - 780. [English translation published in Entomological Review, 2006, 86 (8), 922 - 927.]" type="journal article" year="2006">Gnezdilov &amp; Drosopoulos, 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gnezdilov" box="[151,391,672,695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Gnezdilov, V. M., Holzinger W. E. &amp; Wilson, M. R. (2014) The Western Palaearctic Issidae (Hemiptera, Fulgoroidea): an illustrated checklist and key to genera and subgenera. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute RAS, Vol. 318, Supplement 1, 124 pp." type="book" year="2014">Gnezdilov et al., 2014</bibRefCitation>
). It comprises currently three species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Spinola, 1839" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1839" box="[799,1106,671,695]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Zopherisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tendinosa">
<emphasis box="[799,932,671,695]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Z. tendinosa</emphasis>
(Spinola, 1839)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dlabola, 1974" authorityName="Dlabola" authorityYear="1974" box="[1116,1432,671,695]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Zopherisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penelopae">
<emphasis box="[1116,1254,671,695]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Z. penelopae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola" box="[1268,1424,672,695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Dlabola J. (1974) Zur Taxonomie und Chorologie einiger mediterraner Zikaden. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientarum Hungaricae, 20 (3 - 4), 289 - 308." type="journal article" year="1974">Dlabola, 1974</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gnezdilov et Drosopoulos, 2006" authorityName="Gnezdilov et Drosopoulos" authorityYear="2006" box="[197,680,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Zopherisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="skaloula">
<emphasis box="[197,318,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Z. skaloula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gnezdilov" box="[325,680,706,729]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Gnezdilov, V. M. &amp; Drosopoulos, S. (2006) A new species and a new subspecies of the planthopper family Issidae (Hemiptera, Fulgoroidea) from Greece. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 85 (4), 774 - 780. [English translation published in Entomological Review, 2006, 86 (8), 922 - 927.]" type="journal article" year="2006">Gnezdilov et Drosopoulos, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. According to recent revision of the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Gnezdilov" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Gnezdilov, V. M. &amp; Drosopoulos, S. (2006) A new species and a new subspecies of the planthopper family Issidae (Hemiptera, Fulgoroidea) from Greece. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 85 (4), 774 - 780. [English translation published in Entomological Review, 2006, 86 (8), 922 - 927.]" type="journal article" year="2006">Gnezdilov &amp; Drosopulos, 2006</bibRefCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName box="[221,354,740,764]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Zopherisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tendinosa">
<emphasis box="[221,354,740,764]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Z. tendinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[538,619,741,764]" name="Croatia" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCounty box="[631,829,741,764]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Southern Bulgaria</collectingCounty>
, and 
<collectingMunicipality box="[888,1119,741,764]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Northwestern Greece</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1131,1270,740,764]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Zopherisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penelopae">
<emphasis box="[1131,1270,740,764]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Z. penelopae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from 
<collectingRegion box="[151,297,776,799]" country="Greece" name="Peloponnisos" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Peloponnesus</collectingRegion>
and Southeastern part of continental 
<collectingCountry box="[712,787,776,799]" name="Greece" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Greece</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[804,872,776,799]" country="Greece" name="Attiki" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Attika</collectingRegion>
Province) (
<bibRefCitation author="Dlabola" box="[1002,1161,776,799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Dlabola J. (1974) Zur Taxonomie und Chorologie einiger mediterraner Zikaden. Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientarum Hungaricae, 20 (3 - 4), 289 - 308." type="journal article" year="1974">Dlabola, 1974</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName box="[1231,1351,775,799]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Zopherisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="skaloula">
<emphasis box="[1231,1351,775,799]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Z. skaloula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:886EA600FFC5FFEEFF2F0C8BB197FBE1:051841CDFFC5FFEEFF2F0F5EB126FCB1" box="[151,373,810,833]" country="Croatia" county="Southern Bulgaria" municipality="Northwestern Greece" name="Southeastern Greece" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" stateProvince="Peloponnesus">Southeastern Greece</location>
, including 
<collectingRegion box="[491,641,810,833]" country="Greece" name="Peloponnisos" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Peloponnesus</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,255,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1423616960" location="In" municipality="As" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Peloponnesus" typeStatus="holotype">
<collectingMunicipality box="[199,229,845,868]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">As</collectingMunicipality>
<taxonomicName box="[239,367,844,868]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Issus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[239,367,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Issus analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a female without good specific characters generally supported by the male genitalia, and if it does not represent a distinct species from one of these three species mentioned above, one of the two of them also known from 
<collectingRegion box="[406,552,914,937]" country="Greece" name="Peloponnisos" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Peloponnesus</collectingRegion>
might represent therefore a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1074,1163,913,937]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Issus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[1074,1163,913,937]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">I. analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:886EA600FFC5FFEEFF2F0C8BB197FBE1:051841CDFFC5FFEEFB220FE6B4E3FC59" box="[1178,1200,914,937]" municipality="As" name="In" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" stateProvince="Peloponnesus">In</location>
the future, molecular analysis by comparison of the 
<typeStatus box="[476,522,949,972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[664,751,948,972]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Issus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[664,751,948,972]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">I. analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with these three species might help to solve this issue.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,255,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
In conclusion, although the type specimen has been identified, the mythic species 
<taxonomicName authority="Brulle, 1833" authorityName="Brulle" authorityYear="1833" box="[1111,1386,983,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Issus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[1111,1239,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Issus analis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brulle" box="[1250,1386,984,1007]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="Brulle, G. A. (1833) I. re Partie. Zoologie. Deuxieme Section. Des animaux articules. In: Bory de Saint-Vincent J. B. G. M. 1832 - 1836 - Expedition scientifique de Moree. Section des sciences physiques, III. Levrault F. L., Paris, Strasbourg (France), 400 pp + pl. i - lxxxiii." type="book chapter" year="1833">Brullé, 1833</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
still remains an enigmatic taxon.
</paragraph>
